============================================================
VALIDATION RULES
============================================================

Implement validation in src/lib/resume/validation.ts.

Profile validation:
- fullName is required.
- email is required and must look like a valid email.
- at least one of education, experience, or projects must exist with meaningful data.
- about section is recommended but not required.
- empty optional fields should not block generation.

Job description validation:
- job description is required.
- minimum 100 characters recommended.
- show a friendly warning if too short.

Template validation:
- template must be selected.

Dynamic entry validation:
- Education must have institution and degree if the entry exists.
- Experience must have company and jobTitle if the entry exists.
- Project must have name and description if the entry exists.

Edge cases:
- If optional URLs are empty, do not render them.
- If bullet arrays are empty, do not render blank bullets.
- If a section has no meaningful entries, hide it.
- Prevent generation when required fields are missing.
- Show clear inline validation messages.

============================================================
TAILORING ENGINE LOGIC
============================================================

Create deterministic local tailoring logic in src/lib/resume/tailoring.ts.

It must work even without OpenAI.

The local tailoring engine must:
1. Extract important keywords from the job description.
2. Score experience, projects, skills, education, and certifications against those keywords.
3. Reorder sections based on relevance.
4. Reorder skills so most relevant skills appear first.
5. Rewrite summary using truthful user-provided data.
6. Keep content ATS-friendly.
7. Never invent missing facts.

Implement helper functions:
- normalizeText(text: string): string
- extractKeywords(jobDescription: string): string[]
- scoreTextAgainstKeywords(text: string, keywords: string[]): number
- rankExperience(entries, keywords)
- rankProjects(entries, keywords)
- rankSkills(skills, keywords)
- createTruthfulSummary(profile, keywords, jobDescription)
- buildTailoredResume(profile, jobDescription, templateId): TailoredResume

Keyword extraction should remove common stop words and prioritize:
- job title words
- technical skills
- tools
- frameworks
- certifications
- domain words
- repeated terms from job description

